# aws-cli v2 installer GPG public key — REFRESH TEMPLATE
#
# The toolbox Dockerfile verifies the aws-cli v2 installer's signature against
# AWS's published signing key (a real supply-chain check, not a checksum the
# same server serves). The current key IS vendored in this repo as the colocated
# awscli-public-key.asc — it's public, with its fingerprint documented in-file
# for independent verification. This .example exists to ROTATE that key.
#
# WHEN TO REFRESH: the vendored key expires (currently 2026-07-07), or AWS
# rotates it — after which `gpg --verify` warns/fails and the build breaks.
#
# TO REFRESH the vendored key:
#   1. Open the AWS CLI docs section "Verifying the integrity of your
#      downloaded files" (search: "aws cli gpg public key").
#   2. Copy the PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK shown there.
#   3. Overwrite  containers/toolbox/awscli-public-key.asc  with it (keep a
#      short comment header documenting the new fingerprint + expiry).
#   4. Confirm the fingerprint printed by:  gpg --show-keys awscli-public-key.asc
#      matches the fingerprint AWS lists in those docs, then rebuild.
#
# (To build without a key — not recommended — pass --build-arg AWSCLI_VERIFY=false.)
#
# -----BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
# ...paste AWS's published aws-cli public key here...
# -----END PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
